<DATE>08/15/2009</DATE>
<AUTHOR>Andy Kuchta</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>I have been a Nissan Frontier owner since 1995 and have been very satisfied with the quality and engineering of Nissan vehicles. Recently I began looking at the X- Terra. I was happy to see that Nissan has continued with their quality in workmanship and "thinking of the little things" like the door in the skid plate that allows you access to the oil filter when changing your oil. The interior is well designed and the ride is comfortable. For anyone looking at a mid sized SUV I'd give the X Terra more than just a passing look.</TEXT>
<FAVORITE>Oil filter access and ride.</FAVORITE>
</DOC>
